
'''YouTube and Copyright'''

URL = http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=6486532

=Description=

"Talk of the Nation" recently focused on the issue of copyright law in the new world of social media in a segment titled "On YouTube, Popularity Can Be a Curse." Guests included Jason Fry, assistant managing editor for WSJ.com and James Boyle, William Neal Reynolds Professor of Law and co-founder of the Center for the Study of the Public Domain at Duke Law School and author of Bound By Law, a comic book about intellectual property and fair use. They discussed intellectual property in the information age. We found this to be a very interesting episode of ToTN, and thought you might as well. So, we invite you to take a listen."
